         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>69</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1990"/><citedRange>42</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">like those of the Aiṇeya king-of-wild animals (his) calves. 8. ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a1 #a2 #a3 #a4 #a5 #a6 #a7 #b1 #b2 #b3 #b4 #b5 #b6 #b7"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:jietal1998"/><citedRange>91ff</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1990"/><citedRange>43</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">(like a) banyan tree, of equal proportions, with his height equal (to its width)</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1990"/><citedRange>44</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:pinault2002a"/><citedRange>252</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:winter1985a"/><citedRange>586</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">each single lock of hair grown [and] turned toward the right</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1990"/><citedRange>46</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:knoll1996"/><citedRange>144</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1990"/><citedRange>48</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1990"/><citedRange>48</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1990"/><citedRange>67</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:knoll1996"/><citedRange>141</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... 19. His shoulders are well formed. 20. ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1990"/><citedRange>49</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1990"/><citedRange>50</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1990"/><citedRange>67</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1990"/><citedRange>68</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">23. Very white his teeth. 24 ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a7"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>125, 347</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1990"/><citedRange>52</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1990"/><citedRange>52</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1990"/><citedRange>52</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... 29. ‘[His] eye-lashes like [those] of a bull. 30. on his head an uṣṇīṣa. 31. a white bunch of hair [is] between his eyebrows.</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>221, 355</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1997"/><citedRange>113</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:kolver1965"/><citedRange>61, 116</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1 #b2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1990"/><citedRange>53</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">If all these thirty-two signs are complete in their entirety on his body, then, standing in front of him, without a hint, and in your minds only, you [pl.] must ask him question[s] as follows: …  (cf 91)</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>645</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1990"/><citedRange>54</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1990"/><citedRange>64</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1990"/><citedRange>64</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:kolver1965"/><citedRange>142</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... how old is he? How many Śāstras does he teach to the Brahmin youths? ...</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Wievie