            <p>&lt;project_comment&gt;&lt;p&gt; beginning of &lt;ref type="ms" target="__a6"/&gt; supplemented to read &lt;hi&gt;ṣok-yo ā(r)ky(aṃ)ś āṅkari&lt;/hi&gt; in &lt;bibl&gt;&lt;title corresp="ref:carlingetal2009"/&gt;&lt;citedRange&gt;58&lt;/citedRange&gt;&lt;/bibl&gt; (TI)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;ref type="ms" target="__b5"/&gt; contains sandhi (&lt;hi&gt;wätkālts sn=ālak-wkäṃ&lt;/hi&gt;) in &lt;bibl&gt;&lt;title corresp="ref:carlingetal2009"/&gt;&lt;citedRange&gt;66&lt;/citedRange&gt;&lt;/bibl&gt; (TI)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;ref type="ms" target="__a5"/&gt;, translation: &lt;bibl&gt;&lt;title corresp="ref:carlingetal2009"/&gt;&lt;citedRange&gt;155&lt;/citedRange&gt;&lt;/bibl&gt; has “with well-shaped shoulders”, from Skt. &lt;hi&gt;susaṃvṛttaskandhaḥ&lt;/hi&gt; - which one to choose? &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;beginning of &lt;ref type="ms" target="__a2"/&gt; - &lt;ref type="ms" target="txt:m-yqii4"/&gt; b8 (= &lt;bibl&gt;&lt;title corresp="ref:jietal1998"/&gt;&lt;citedRange&gt;84&lt;/citedRange&gt;&lt;/bibl&gt;) has &lt;hi&gt;ṣtāmm&lt;/hi&gt; with a neutral t! (TI)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;ref type="ms" target="__a2"/&gt; to be supplemented with &lt;hi&gt;nya(grot)&lt;/hi&gt;... &lt;hi&gt;[tä](preṃ kapśiñño&lt;/hi&gt;; translation above = &lt;bibl&gt;&lt;title corresp="ref:carlingetal2009"/&gt;&lt;citedRange&gt;209&lt;/citedRange&gt;&lt;/bibl&gt;, while &lt;bibl&gt;&lt;title corresp="ref:jietal1998"/&gt;&lt;citedRange&gt;85&lt;/citedRange&gt;&lt;/bibl&gt; (for &lt;ref type="ms" target="txt:m-yqii4"/&gt; b8) und &lt;bibl&gt;&lt;title corresp="ref:carlingetal2009"/&gt;&lt;citedRange&gt;133&lt;/citedRange&gt;&lt;/bibl&gt; both have “with his height equal to its arm span” (TI)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;ref type="ms" target="__b2"/&gt;: &lt;hi&gt;ko(s)[pr](eṃ) manarkāśśi śāsträntu ākläṣ&lt;/hi&gt; translated as above in &lt;bibl&gt;&lt;title corresp="ref:carlingetal2009"/&gt;&lt;citedRange&gt;36&lt;/citedRange&gt;&lt;/bibl&gt; (“How many Śāstras does he teach to the Brahmin youths?”); ibid: 210 and in &lt;bibl&gt;&lt;title corresp="ref:jietal1998"/&gt;&lt;citedRange&gt;91&lt;/citedRange&gt;&lt;/bibl&gt; the translation runs “How many Brahmin youths does he teach the śāstras?” (TI)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/project_comment&gt;</p>
